column5: Lets do a little survey. Whats your favorite destination in NW Ontario. I do not mean body of water, or lodge resort, but city, town, or hamlet. Rainy River, Nestor Falls, Fort Frances, Sioux Narrows, Kenora, or in the Red Lake area. And why? What's your worse place you would visit? And why? Play nice, but be candid on this.
I have been near Red lake for many years and now Ear Falls. Not sure I would catagorize as my favorite place. they have groceries, gas and booze. good enough for me. Ft. Frances stinks.
Sturgeon Lake..........The one near Savant Lake. Awesome fishing and 96% underfished !!!!!!!
I didn't mention Sturgeon Lake. He didn't want names of lakes.
Anywhere north of MN or WI...that's my favorite part of Ontario.
I'm thinking Centerfolds in T.Bay by far. :)
